metadata.name: Context-Free Wind #4
metadata.description:
Context-Free Wind is a poetry generator and visualizer created by Ross Goodwin (https://rossgoodwin.com) in vanilla JavaScript without the use of any framework or external libraries, excluding code required by fxhash. The generator uses a custom context-free grammar algorithm and word lists assembled by the creator to produce (...admittedly, fairly strange...) sentences.

These sentences are then blown aloft by a procedural "wind" -- based on the algorithm Goodwin first explored in the following Dweet:
https://www.dwitter.net/d/23927

metadata.name: Chaotic Neutral #177
metadata.description:
'Chaotic Neutral' by pixelwank 
A fun mixture of 10print inspired patterns, spiralling shapes and masking. 

Sometimes more minimal, often chaotic and maximal.

I wanted this work to be confronting at times, make the viewer zoom in and get lost in the chaos. 
And on the flipside, zoom out and let the eyes wander around the piece, guided by the motion of the patterns and feel a sense of calm.

Variety of palettes, grid sizing, strokeweights, blendmodes and more. 

5 possible aspect ratios with 3:4 being most common. 

10% of primary sales are going straight to the Waiting To Be Signed wallet as a donation and thankyou for always delivering great content on the fxhash ecosystem with their podcast <3

50% of royalties to the minter. 
In live mode press 's' or 'S' to save higher resolution image. Contact me via twitter if you want a super hi-res file. 

Copyright pixelwank 2022.
Made with love and p5js 

Thanks for collecting!
Big shoutout to the Circolors fam. Don't worry something's cooking <3 

Remember. It's. For. Fun.
R.I.F.F. 
<3

metadata.name: an abstract concept #116
metadata.description:
I often try to duplicate my IRL analog abstract painting in code, and this, like my previous mint "a fleeting moment," is an attempt at that. Or it started that way. As is usual with such things, it quickly took on a life of its own. 

The algorithm itself consists of three layers of the main particle abstraction, which comes in five different styles, and roughly eight layers of the "texture," which comes in three styles. The palette consists of the background color and three colors for the particle algorithm. The texture is always drawn with the first of those three colors (the "base" color.) 

The result is indicative of my normal painting style (I almost always use three color layers over a background color, and paint with a spatula, palette knife, or cake knife) but is its own unique look.

This collection is Jimena + Marcosâ€™ first generative art collection in the Tezos blockchain via FX Hash, and consists of 222 1/1 artworks created with javascript.

metadata.name: Secret Garden #39
metadata.description:
Secret Garden

This secret garden, which does not exist anywhere else, is a secret space found in the brain of AI, that is, in the latent space. Would the AI â€‹â€‹that created these mysterious gardens have memories of the scent of flowers in its brain?
No matter how well a machine imitates the human learning process, it has inherent limitations. Humans remember the situation by comprehensively utilizing the five senses, including not only the visual information of the flowers, but also the melodies that flowed at that moment, the buzzing of flying bees, the dizzying scent of flowers, and the warm sunlight. However, this AI only does fractional numerical calculations using only the given pixel RGB values.

Humans with much more complex brains and computational systems are passionate about the images that AI creates. However, if you think about it a little, it seems that this interest may be a kind of leisurely relaxation for mature beings to watch the development of immature beings.
This AI doesn't even know what it just built.


* Draw algorithmic strokes by reference the color of AI-generated flower garden.
* One of 832 AI-generated seed images are randomly selected.
* No property(traits), no rarity

[Left click on the screen] : add strokes (Temporarily retouching)
[S] Save to file

Made with Love & P5.js & P5.beizer !

By CSLIM, 2022

metadata.name: Vistas #54
metadata.description:
Vistas is an exploration in using layers to build an abstracted geometric landscape using a generative algorithm. But in a way that not only creates a digital image but also allows for the creation of an IRL physical artwork made from the 18 layers of laser cut wood. 

All mints created in first day will receive a free physical woodcut valued at ~$250. Up to 10% of all other mints may randomly get a free physical as well. 

Learn more about physicals: https://alleditions.art/p/vistas

The canvas for each output may be one of three different orientations, a square, portrait, or landscape. The portrait and landscape orientations create physicals that are 7.5 x 11.5 inches and square orientations create 7.5 x 7.5 inch physicals. 

The resulting output is carefully designed so that it can be exploded into discreet layers (Shift-E) and exported as an SVG (Shift-S) so it can be used to laser cut or plot an IRL physical artwork. 

A variety of elements are used to construct each unique one of a kind landscape. Sun, moon, sunbeams, stars, clouds, mountains, hills, plains, beaches, fields, water, boats, rocks, trees, and even mysterious obelisks. 



UTILITY

Shift - P to export a PNG
Shift - E explode the layers
Shift - S export a vector SVG

Slide the layers with the arrow keys. Click and drag the mouse to move the light source and adjust the layer shadows.

QUERY STRINGS

Add &screws=true to render with screw holes for cutting in order to assemble a physical with chicago screws.

Adjust the size of the output by adding &x=1150 and/or &y=1150 to adjust the physical size of the output where 100 = 1 inch.

metadata.name: Amplitude #208
metadata.description:
Amplitude is a study in depth. Waves travel across the frame using Perlin noise to guide its modulation. Allowing slight variations to occur in each layer. Sometimes the waves are added to the frame and sometimes they are subtracted. Resulting in dramatically different visual appearances. 

Like most of my work this piece is carefully designed to also exist IRL as a 12 layer laser carved woodcut. 
https://alleditions.art/p/amplitude

Arrow keys - adjust the perspective

DESIGNED FOR IRL
Shift P - for a PNG
Shift E - to explode the layers
Shift S - for an SVG

metadata.name: A24Z #919
metadata.description:
Every artist and collector feels the joy of both creating and collecting. But if I could share the joy of creating with collectors. And collectors with their family and friends, what may be an additive process of joy is now perhaps exponential. Joy to the power of 26 to be exact. 

In this work I invite my friends and collectors to collaborate with me. Though not in coding, but together in a process of creating narratives and visuals. Code and story. We didnâ€™t use github, just a simple p5.js editor to try out different programs and palettes. Pedrofe and J0rdan pick their palettes tastefully and carefully. okeoke, perhaps more of a genius than he lets on, picks his palettes blind. No hex color picker. Just straight up rhymes.  

In our discussions verbal language was forbidden. Only emojis were allowed to express our tastes and views. Each emojis put down on google doc was taken with absolutely seriousness. 

Pedro: Loves to taking his daily walks on â€œMagic Mushroom Mountainâ€

J0rdan: Wonders about â€œQuark Question Quichesâ€

Okeoke: Just get lost in â€œFinnegansâ€™ Flower Fields.â€

It has been a great joy to present our illustration book A24Z, 8 more than you know who. Each page expresses the alphabet with the best of our knowledge in semantics and sarcasm. Collect just 1 page, collect the alphabets that spell out your name, collect the whole A to Z. Read it to your children or loved ones. Though you might need to interpolate or extrapolate with great imagination which children all have. But most importantly, like all children, have fun!

Press 1 to save png, only for Chrome, not Safari. Preview images are compressed or broken, test capture at 300 sec.
